locks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "The user requires two main outputs: a SystemVerilog interface matching the golden testbench\'s instantiation needs, and an improved golden testbench. \\n\\n**1. Interface Generation:**\\nThe input specification defines `TopModule` with only `output out`. However, the golden testbench instantiates `TopModule top_module1 ( .out(out_dut) );`. The interface must reflect this structure. Since the DUT has one output, the interface will define one output port.\\n\\n**2. Testbench Improvement:**\\n*   **Functionality Maintenance:** The core functionality (clock generation, module instantiation, error counting logic, timeout, and final summary display) must be kept exactly as per the provided `<previous_tb>`.\\n*   **Golden Testbench Contradiction:** The golden testbench uses `stimulus_gen`, `RefModule`, and `TopModule`. The testbench must maintain these instantiations.\\n*   **Error Counting:** The logic for `stats1.errors` and `stats1.errors_out` must be preserved.\\n*   **Final Display:** The final check must display \\"SIMULATION PASSED\\" if no mismatch occurs, or \\"SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y\\" otherwise.\\n*   **First Mismatch Display:** The requirement to display detailed signals (inputs, outputs, expected output) upon the *first* mismatch must be implemented. The previous code attempted this but had structural issues. I will refine the logic within the `always @(posedge clk, negedge clk)` block to correctly detect the very first time `!tb_match` is true AND `stats1.errors` is 0 (before incrementing).\\n*   **Syntax/Logic Fixes in Previous TB:**\\n    *   Line 44 in the previous TB had `tend` instead of `end`. This must be fixed.\\n    *   Line 88 used `$display("\t,"` which is invalid concatenation/syntax for the final display block. This must be corrected to standard SystemVerilog $display format.\\n    *   The structure for capturing mismatch details needs to be robust, ensuring it triggers only once.\\n*   **Output Display Logic:** The detailed display logic needs to be refined. I will use a dedicated flag (`first_mismatch_detected`) to ensure the detailed output only happens exactly once, when the first error is registered.\\n*   **HEX/BIN Formatting:** The requirement to display HEX and BIN formats for multi-bit signals is handled by using `%h` and `%b` format specifiers, which is already present in the previous TB\'s attempt.\\n\\n**Advice to avoid syntax errors:**\\n1.  Always check that `endmodule` matches every `module` keyword.\\n2.  Ensure all initial blocks and always blocks have correct sensitivity lists and termination (`end`).\\n3.  Be careful with scope and variable access (e.g., ensuring `stats1` is used consistently, fixing typos like `sstats1`).\\n4.  When implementing complex displays, ensure the string literals and format specifiers are correctly paired to avoid missing quotes, as seen in the failed log.\\n\\n**Implementation Details:**\\n1.  The `TopModule` interface is minimal, matching the specification.\\n2.  The testbench will be heavily modified from the previous version to correctly implement the requested enhanced logging while respecting the complex structure of the golden testbench logic. The final status check will use `stats1.errors` and `stats1.errortime` as required by the prompt\'s final display rule, rather than the separate `stats1.errors_out` logic, to conform to the requested final output format.\\n\\n*Self-Correction on Final Display:* The prompt requires: \\"ADD DISPLAY \\"SIMULATION PASSED\\" if no mismatch occurs, otherwise display: \\"SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y\\".\\" This refers to the *overall* mismatch count (`stats1.errors`), which is captured in the final `initial` block, fulfilling the core requirement, regardless of the detailed output logging.\\n\\n*Refining the First Mismatch Display:* I will trigger the detailed display when `!tb_match` and `stats1.errors` increments from 0 to 1, ensuring we capture the state exactly at that clock edge where the mismatch is first observed.\\n\\n*Code Cleanup:* Correcting the typo `sstats1` to `stats1` in the error counting logic, and fixing the structural issues from the previous attempt, especially in the final output blocks, to adhere strictly to the required final summary format."\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n 